turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why did you invite her here?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why? Does that bother you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's been in New York for three-and-a-half years. She don't just suddenly come and-

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, maybe, maybe he just wanted to see her.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You don't travel seven hundred miles just to see.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you mean? They lived next door to each other their entire lives. Why shouldn't he want to see her? Hey, don't look at me like that. I don't know anymore than you do.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: He's not going to marry her.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know he's even thinking about it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's got that about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, so what?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What's going on here, Joe?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Listen, kid-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's not Larry's girl. She knows that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can't read her mind.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Then why is she married? Then why isn't she married? She's been in New York and there's hundreds of single men there.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm sure hundreds of them asked her and told her that she's foolish, but no.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's waited.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know why she's waited?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because she thinks like me, that's why.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's faithful as a rock, don't you know. In my worst moments I can think of her-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I think again, that I'm-I'm right.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look, it's a nice day. What are we arguing for?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody in my house better ever dare-dare to challenge her faith. Maybe strangers, but not his father, not his brother.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because he's not coming back. Then what do I got to live for? I'll kill myself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't, don't laugh at me, don't laugh at me.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Look at it. Because why, when she came here and she slept in his room, the memorial broke into pieces. Look at it, look at it, Joe.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: All right. All right. Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You got to believe, believe with me because I can't stand all alone.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Okay. Just calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, you've got to believe.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Believe, Joe. You above all people have got to believe.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why me, above all?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Huh?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why me above all?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You got to keep believing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look at you, you're shaking.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I can't help it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What have I got to hide?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Huh? What the hell's the matter with you, Kate?
